Introduction

In this project, we will try to estimate the difference in trading data in the Turkish electricity market, that is, the imbalance values on a daily basis.In doing so, we will use two different datasets: Bulk-imbalance and Weather files. After developing the model, we will try to predict the hourly imbalance values for the next day’s 12 hours using the daily data. Actually, what we need to do is to find system direction. If the bulk imbalance value is less than -50, system direction is negative;if between -50 and +50, it will be neutral; If it is more than +50, it will be positive.

In our project, as a step, 1) To adapt and combine 2 different datasets for modelling 2) Creating a simple time series model 3) Develop the model (with EBLR) 4) get the results next day.

As seen in the tree, the rightmost path causes many errors. That’s why we focus on this part first.And we add our newly created decision variables to the model.Thus, we obtain a new model with better results. Then, we re-examine the residual values of this new model by creating a tree.

We repeat this process until our improvement is very low. The process: -Create a model -Examine the tree for residuals -Create decision variables cause many errors -Add the decision varianles to model and re-evaluate the new model

Submission

As mentioned before, we need to submit by estimating the system direction data, not the net bulk imbalance values. Therefore, we need to create system direction values from the imbalance values we estimated.

tmp2 = tmp2 %>% 
  mutate(predicted_diretion = 
           case_when(predicted < -50 ~ "Negative" ,
                     predicted>=-50 & predicted<=50 ~ "Neutral" ,
                     predicted> 50 ~ "Positive" )
         )
